data.enText: the hard reddish-brown wood of a tropical tree, used for making furniture
skin tanned to a deep mahogany

tr: a shade of brown with a tinge of red
any of various tropical timber trees of the family Meliaceae especially the genus Swietinia valued for their hard yellowish- to reddish-brown wood that is readily worked and takes a high polish
wood of any of various mahogany trees
much used for cabinetwork and furniture

value.def: Mahogany is a dark reddish-brown wood that is used to make furniture.
value.tran: (用来制造家具的)红木，桃花心木
